Nigerian President Goodluck Jonathan
plans to reduce the number of ministers in his Cabinet to 36
from 42,  ThisDay  reported, citing an unidentified person in the
presidentâ€™s office.  Jonathan will make the changes following his inauguration
on May 29, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  Jonathan, 53, a Christian from the oil-rich Niger River
delta region, defeated his closest rival,  Muhammadu Buhari , a
northern Muslim, in the April 16 presidential election.  To contact the reporter on this story:
